{{Quote|Shantipole?''"<br />"''Every pilot in the galaxy knows that's a one-way trip.|Two [[Phoenix Squadron]] pilots|<ref name="Wings of the Master" />}}
'''Shantipole''' was a remote [[planet]] located in [[the galaxy]]'s [[Mid Rim Territories|Mid Rim]] that was renowned for having a violent [[atmosphere]] and being a one-way trip for [[pilot]]s. It was home to the [[Mon Calamari]] [[Quarrie]], who designed a [[Prototype B6|prototype]] for the [[A/SF-01 B-wing starfighter|B-wing starfighter]]. During the [[blockade of Ibaar]], [[Hera Syndulla]], [[Sabine Wren]], and [[Garazeb Orrelios]] traveled to Shantipole to get the prototype B-wing to break [[Ibaar]]'s [[blockade]].<ref name="Wings of the Master" />

==Description==
A remote world<ref name="Epic Battles">''[[Star Wars Rebels: Visual Guide: Epic Battles]]''</ref> located in the [[Shantipole system]] in the [[Roche sector]] of the [[Mid Rim Territories]]<ref name="Appendix" /> along the [[Perlemian Trade Route]]<ref name="Map" /> Shantipole was [[orbit]]ed by at least one [[moon]]<ref name="Wings of the Master" /> and had a violent [[atmosphere]] of [[gas]] and lightning, and thus was considered practically desolate. The [[planet]]'s surface was dominated by [[mountain]] spires<ref name="Shantipole" /> covered with vibrantly [[color]]ed [[tree]]s.<ref name="Wings of the Master" /> Large, winged creatures known as [[dactillion]]s could be found in Shantipole's skies.<ref name="Dactillion" />

==History==
[[File:HeraSyndullaASF-01B-Wing-SWX_Joshua_Cairos.png|thumb|right|300px|Hera Syndulla tested the Prototype B6 in the volatile atmosphere of Shantipole.]]
Shantipole was once a highly prospected source of rare gases similar to [[tibanna]], though investors abandoned Shantipole due to its unpredictable wind patterns.<ref name="DoR" /> Because of that violent atmosphere, most [[pilot]]s typically avoided Shantipole,<ref name="Shantipole" /> with one regarding it as a "one-way trip."<ref name="Wings of the Master" /> This attribute, however, made it the perfect workplace for [[Quarrie]], a [[Mon Calamari]] master [[engineer]] and [[starfighter]] designer, as it allowed him to toil on his creations far from the watchful [[eye]] of the [[Galactic Empire]].<ref name="Shantipole" /> He established a [[Shantipole landing field|secret starfighter laboratory]] and,<ref name="Epic Battles" /> after [[Standard year|years]] of work, he designed and built [[Prototype B6]],<ref name="Shantipole" /> an advanced starfighter armed with experimental weapons, with the assistance of his [[astromech droid]], [[BG-81]].<ref name="Epic Battles" />

==Behind the scenes==
Shantipole made its first [[canon]]ical appearance in the ''[[Star Wars Rebels]]'' [[Star Wars Rebels Season Two|Season Two]] episode "[[Wings of the Master]],"<ref name="Wings of the Master" /> which premiered on [[Disney XD]] on [[November 11]], [[2015]].<ref name="Wings release">{{WebCite|url=http://affiliate.zap2it.com/tv/star-wars-rebels/EP018796240036?aid=dxd|text=Star Wars Rebels: Wings of the Master|work=Disney XD Official Schedule|archiveurl=https://archive.is/1Ac08}}</ref> [[Research Station Shantipole]] had previously appeared located on an asteroid in the [[1988]]<ref name="YBY">''[[Star Wars Year By Year: A Visual History, New Edition]]''</ref> [[West End Games]] adventure book ''[[Strike Force: Shantipole]]'', which is part of [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]].<ref name="SFS">''[[Strike Force: Shantipole]]''</ref>

Shantipole subsequently appeared in the non-canon [[2017]] ''[[LEGO Star Wars: The Freemaker Adventures]]'' [[LEGO Star Wars: The Freemaker Adventures Season Two|Season Two]] episodes "[[Free Fall]]" and "[[Return of the Return of the Jedi]]." In those episodes, the [[Freemakers/LEGO|Freemakers]] and Quarrie lure the Imperial [[Hunter droid/LEGO|hunter droid]] [[M-OC/LEGO|M-OC]] into a [[Skirmish on Shantipole|trap on Shantipole]], resulting in the destruction of the [[Arrowhead (Freemakers)|''Arrowhead'']] and the ''[[StarScavenger]]''. After M-OC survives and escapes to fortify the [[DS-2 Death Star II Mobile Battle Station|second Death Star]],<ref name="Free Fall">{{FreemakerAdventures|Free Fall}}</ref> the Freemakers rebuild the ''StarScavenger'' and participate in the [[Battle of Endor]], defeating M-OC.<ref name="ROTROTJ">{{FreemakerAdventures|Return of the Return of the Jedi}}</ref>

